Instruction: With the new good battery installed and all module switches ON and the load connected, measure the voltage directly across the battery terminals again, then measure the current drawn from the battery by inserting an ammeter in series with the battery. Compare the loaded battery voltage to the expected ~12 V and note whether the battery voltage collapses toward 0 V under load (indicating a high current path/short) or remains near 12 V with almost no current (indicating an open circuit or extremely high resistance somewhere in the supply path).
